27 f. me truncus, etc.: cf. 2, the indicative emphasizes the certainty of Hor- ace's fate which was suddenly averted by Faunus. Cf. 3, 16, 3.

28 f. Faunus: the kindly wood- land spirit, who loved to visit Horace's farm and to care for his flocks (1, 17), is named here as protector.
